metadata.name: Heat Death #831
metadata.description:
Heat Death is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

It aims to produce variation and detail from minimal logic.

The source code uses p5.js and consists of around 180 lines of code. It has been left unminified for the interested viewer to learn more.

metadata.name: Dencity #837
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Particularization #6
metadata.description:
“Particularization” is the seventh collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

All concepts can be viewed from different levels. You can focus on the details, leaving out the generalized result but understanding the finer points. Or you could emphasize the concept as a whole, comprehending it well overall but missing out on the specifics. It's impossible to choose both, you have to figure out which approach works best for each scenario.

metadata.name: Dually #30
metadata.description:
Each mint is audioreactive visuals paired with a beat that has a dual nature: you might start with a slightly more “sinister” vibe or a slightly “bouncy” vibe, which sets the tone with the beat's bassline and the colors of the visualization

From there, the “instruments” are features that pull from a set of possible variants. The beat that you end up with when you mint is layered together from those features

All of these audio tracks are composed by hand the old-fashioned human-made way using sampling, synths, soul, and Ableton Live

The visualization is one of seven variants and is are driven by the instruments in the beat

Click to pause and mute, or to see what rad visual moments you can capture

P5.js + chroma.js + Tone.js + beats

metadata.name: Boids 2D #168
metadata.description:
'Boids 2D' is a Generative Token that represent the flocking of birds over a landscape. The name 'Boids' comes from a famous computer animation / simulation program.

The landscape is rendered as a texture using a kind of warped noise as height map.

The boids are disposed along the flow lines obtained from the noise gradient. This gives the sensation that the Boids follow the undulations of the landscape.

Previously embedded in the 'Boids' (3D) Generative Token as an ester egg on 20% of iterations, now every iterations will be 2D as viewed from the sky.

Every owner of the 'Boids' (3D) GT will receive one 'Boids 2D' for free. The owner that minted a 'Boids' with ester egg will receive two 'Boids 2D' for free.

It is possible to save a 1600x1600 png with key 's'.

Sources of variations are:
- Noise warping control parameters generating different grade of complexity and different shape an the landscape and Boids flock (combined on a single number on the features).
- 21 color mapping for landscape and Boids.
- Two kind of border, solid or negative.

Features:
Palette: color palette name (21 different palettes)
NoiseControl: noise control parameter (0 - 15)
Border: the border can be in solid color or negative color (Solid, Negative)


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Origin-a-tions II: Formation #96
metadata.description:
Nothing stays the same as they first origin-a-ted. Things are constantly changing from one form to another. Only those who can see all these formation steps in order can really grasp the true nature of things.

Origin-a-tions is a three-parts series of generative artwork, started with Part I: Creation and continuing now with Part II: Formation, that depicts one possible variation of how things may be originating.

* * *

20 reserved pieces will be sent as gift to collectors who minted 4 or more pieces of Origin-a-tions I: Creation.

Press S to save as PNG.

Made by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART
Made with: JavaScript + HTML Canvas
License: LICENSE.txt
